This folder stores helper scripts for looking up a user's profile and manager via Microsoft Graph.

PowerShell (preferred)
1. Run in PowerShell 7:
   ./test_find_my_boss.ps1 -User "okada.kazuhito@jp.panasonic.com"

   If the browser redirect to localhost fails, switch to the device-code flow:
   ./test_find_my_boss.ps1 -User "okada.kazuhito@jp.panasonic.com" -UseDeviceAuth

   To dump the full user/manager payload as JSON instead of formatted lists:
   ./test_find_my_boss.ps1 -User "okada.kazuhito@jp.panasonic.com" -Raw

   Required delegated scopes: User.Read.All, Directory.Read.All (admin consent usually needed).

Python (optional)
1. Install dependencies:
   pip install msal requests
2. Set environment variables for your registered app:
   set MSAL_CLIENT_ID=<client id>
   set MSAL_TENANT_ID=<tenant id>
3. Execute with device-code auth:
   python .\test_find_my_boss.py --user okada.kazuhito@jp.panasonic.com

Refer to the comments at the top of each script for additional details.
